article.description: Darius Williams converted 9 of 10 from the line and scored 14 points as Prairie View A&M won its second straight game to open Southwestern Conference play, topping Southern 64-54 on Monday night.
article.headline: Prairie View wins 2nd straight in SWAC, tops Southern 64-54
article.linkText: Prairie View wins 2nd straight in SWAC, tops Southern 64-54
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Darius Williams converted 9 of 10 from the line and scored 14 points as Prairie View A&M won its second straight game to open Southwestern Conference play, topping Southern 64-54 on Monday night. The Panthers, who built their 10-point margin in the first half to take a 32-22 advantage at intermission, now have won three straight after snapping a four-game losing streak. Devonte Patterson added 10 points for Prairie View (6-9, 2-0). Damiree Burns scored 12 points for Southern (3-12, 0-2), which now has lost eight straight games.
